events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 20 points with 12 rebounds and RJ Barrett had 19 and 11 on Sunday to help the New York Knicks snap a five-game losing streak and beat the Boston Celtics 105-75.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kemba Walker returns, but Knicks blow out Celtics 105-75

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 29 points and 10 rebounds, Garrett Temple scored 15 of his season-high 21 points in the second quarter and the Chicago Bulls ended a four-game losing streak with a 117-101 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls roll past Mavs 117-101 to end 4-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Reserve Jordan Clarkson scored 23 points, Donovan Mitchell added 18 and the Utah Jazz beat the Nuggets 109-105 Sunday night in a rematch of their thrilling first-round playoff series last season that Denver captured in seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson helps Jazz to 5th straight, beat Nuggets 109-105

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson had 31 points and six rebounds, Steven Adams made a pair of clutch free throws with 17.9 seconds remaining, and the New Orleans Pelicans overcame a 43-point performance by Sacramento’s De’Aaron Fox and beat the Kings 128-123 Sunday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson, Pelicans spoil Fox's big night in win over Kings

headlines.description: — Marcus Morris Sr. scored a season-high 20 points to lead seven players in double figures, and the Los Angeles Clippers defeated the Indiana Pacers 129-96 on Sunday night for their first four-game winning streak of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers beat Pacers 129-96 for 1st 4-game winning streak
